		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2018 SI"></a><br><code>sle2018s/paper02</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2018 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>MORBIG: A Static Parser for POSIX Shell</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/YannRégisGianas.html">Yann Régis-Gianas</a>, <a href="../profile/NicolasJeannerod.html">Nicolas Jeannerod</a>, <a href="../profile/RalfTreinen.html">Ralf Treinen</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cola.2020.100944">10.1016/j.cola.2020.100944</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="../sle2018/paper18.html"><em>Morbig: a static parser for POSIX shell</em></a> (SLE 2018)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagM">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The main contribution is a static parser for POSIX shell that resolves shell-specific syntactic challenges, i.e., a compilation-style front-end component.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3d.html"><span class="tagL">T3D: GPLs</span></a><ul><li> The work targets the POSIX shell language, a widely used general-purpose scripting/programming language.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> The paper validates correctness/practicality via substantial evaluation on real-world scripts and comparisons against existing implementations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<footer/>
